<item>
            <title>[LU-10915] Draining QP</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-10915</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Currently o2iblnd waits until all the WR have completed before destroying the connection.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;However, there is no time limit to the completion operation so we can have indefinite waits.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Adopt a new draining QP mechanism introduced by MLX to handle that situation.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Refer to:&lt;br/&gt;
 &lt;a href=&quot;https://wiki.hpdd.intel.com/display/LNet/Adapt+to+latest+RDMA+changes&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://wiki.whamcloud.com/display/LNet/Adapt+to+latest+RDMA+changes&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
